FBIS3-35298 "drnes036_n_94009" FBIS-NES-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 LEBANON Palestinian Killed in Sidon for `Moral Reasons' NC2302120994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1115 GMT 23 Feb 94 NC2302120994 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] In Sidon today, Palestinian Muhammad Sa'id al-Sayigh was killed and his daughters Ruwaydah and Rana wounded when explosives placed under the driver's seat in his Toyota went off. There was an estimated half a kg of explosives. Our correspondent learned that the crime was committed for moral reasons and that the deceased had distributed pornographic films that prompted opposition from Islamic groups in Sidon.
